reviewText: Vdeo was right on time , brand new.
Great DVD! The youth team that I coach loved it.
good for a short et trip

I am not a footie fan, but some of my family members are.  I figured that this would be fun to watch in the run up to the cup.  So, if your household is going to be caught up in Cup Madness, this might offer a bit of fun and you may even pick up some interesting info.

I had ordered this for my soccer-fanatic 11 year old son (who is half Dutch, so it's his cultural obligation!). We're all soccer fans, and I hoped it would be great family viewing. His review, however, was that it was 'kind of boring - probably better for Papa'. So if you're into soccer history and reliving the moments, go for it. But kids are probably more into the here and now of the sport.
It was purchased as a gift and they said they liked it. Hopefully they weren't just trying to be nice!
